#. <section class="sutta" id="sn29.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn29.11-20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 29"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 29"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn29.11-20:0.2"
msgid "1. Nāgavagga"
msgstr "1. Dragons"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11–​20. Aṇḍajadānūpakārasuttadasaka → annadāyakaaṇḍajasuttaṃ (bj) | dānupakāra 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn29.11-20:0.3"
msgid "11–​20. Aṇḍajadānūpakārasuttadasaka"
msgstr "11–20. Ten Discourses On How Giving Helps to Become Egg-Born"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.245"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn29.11-20:1.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:1.2"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body "
"breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā "
"dvayakārī."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, it’s when someone does both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and "
"mind."

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.2"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.3"
msgid "‘aṇḍajā nāgā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti."
msgstr "‘The egg-born dragons are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.4"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the egg-born dragons!’"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.6"
msgid "So annaṃ deti."
msgstr "They give food …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.7"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu … pe … upapajjatīti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.9"
msgid "so pānaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "drink …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.10"
msgid "vatthaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "clothing …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.11"
msgid "yānaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "a vehicle …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.12"
msgid "mālaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "a garland …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.13"
msgid "gandhaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "fragrance …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.14"
msgid "vilepanaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "makeup …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.15"
msgid "seyyaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "a bed …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.16"
msgid "āvasathaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "a house …"

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.17"
msgid "padīpeyyaṃ deti."
msgstr "a lamp."

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.18"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the "
"egg-born dragons."

msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.19"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks "
"up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn29.11-20:2.20"
msgid "Vīsatimaṃ."
msgstr ""
